record.Title: Mount Rainier viewed from Mount Beljica, Washington, ca. 1907
record.Notes: Note on negative sleeve: Beljika view man with rifle. Taken from Mount Beljica, a 5,486-ft. peak a mile west of the Mount Rainier National Park boundary five miles northeast of Ashford in southeast Pierce County. The first name was Beljacka Mountain and was named by a pioneer settler named Mesler who used the initials of the first names of his children and some of their friends who went on a hike on the mountain in July, 1897.
record.SubjectsLCSH: Rainier, Mount (Wash.)

record.Notes: On verso of image: Thurston County Court House as old State Capitol building. Built in 1892 of stone from nearby Tenino, it is located on Franklin Street between Legion Way and Seventh Avenue. It was used as the Thurston County Courthouse until about 1900 when it became the Capitol. It was restored in 1980 and now house the offices of the Superintendent of Public Instruction.
